Introduction Games require two things:
Fast code It needs to be fast enough to render graphics and simulate physics all within one game tick. It needs to be able to support more complex mechanics, AI, and networking (for multiplayer games). It needs to be performant on a large range of devices that may have suboptimal hardware like consoles&hellip;
Safe code It needs to support unloading and loading game objects frequently. It needs to load files from CDNs, disk, and cache.
